article.headline: Auburn 74, Delaware 46
article.story: CAROLINA, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Nathan Watson scored 19 points and Tony Douglas added 13 in the second half to lead Auburn to a 74-46 win over Delaware in the San Juan Shootout tournament Monday. The Tigers (7-3), who led 31-25 at halftime, went on a 27-10 run in the final 10 minutes of the second half to close the game. Douglas led the spurt with nine points, including eight consecutive points in a 2-minute stretch near the end of the game. The Blue Hens (4-4) outrebounded Auburn 41-27, including a 18-8 edge in offensive rebounds, but had 26 turnovers that Auburn converted into 33 points. Watson was 5-of-8 from 3-point range, and Quinnel Brown added 18 points for Auburn. Rulon Washington led Delaware with 12 points, and Raphael Madera had 10.
